<img src="http://www.hobbyflite.com/images/push_cloud.JPG"> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 8:40:17 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimmy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Here's the deal</span><hr size=1> Wizards have more AE spells than any other kind of spell in our book.  No joking, although ports have gained on them significantly in the last few months.  There are more AE spells than blasts.  Further, these AE spells are fairly evenly distributed through our spellbook, in a rough pattern of PBAE/Rain/Column/Al'Kabor with some exceptions.  This pattern fills out the spell book steadily as you go up levels.<br>
<br>
There's two problems with this.  First, AE Rains are broken, as admitted by Verant, and aren't going to be fixed.  Second, we have a line of spells in Al'Kabor that is so terrible it is not an upgrade when we get them, it is a downgrade, even though its higher level.<br>
<br>
Here are two examples:<br>
<br>
Pillar of Fire<br>
Level 16<br>
Mana 84<br>
Damage 76<br>
Damage/Mana on max targets (4) 3.62<br>
<br>
Fire Spiral of Al’Kabor<br>
Level 20<br>
Mana 150<br>
Damage 76<br>
Damage/Mana on max targets (5) 3.04<br>
<br>
======and=======<br>
<br>
Pillar of Frost<br>
Level 51<br>
Mana 325<br>
Damage 800<br>
Damage/Mana max targets (4) 9.85<br>
<br>
Inferno of Al’Kabor<br>
Level 53<br>
Damage 625<br>
Mana 800<br>
Damage/Mana max targets (5) 7.68<br>
<br>
That's just two examples, I had the entire line listed with the nearest pillar line (the closest equivalent spell) but the post has rolled off.<br>
<br>
OK lets analyze this: <br>
level 16 spell does 76 damage for 84 mana to 4 targets<br>
level 20 spell does 76 damage for 150 mana to 5 targets.  That's 4 levels higher, same damage, almost double the mana.  The radius is larger, and it has a slight interrupt pushback component (about as reliable as shock of lightning on NPCs).  This is a rotten spell that is not useful for anyone in any normal endeavor.<br>
<br>
level 51 spell does 800 damage to 4 targets for 325 mana<br>
level 53 spell does 800 damage to 5 targets for 625 mana.<br>
<br>
Now, even at level 53, 625 mana is a whale load, and its nearly double the mana cost of a spell 2 hell levels earlier, for the single added target and larger radius.<br>
<br>
So here we have the 'upgrades' to fill out our spell pool in our most numerous spell line, the line Verant certainly acts like they meant to be our defining power (at least after we pointed out AE spells).  But the upgrades are crap, they don't do anything better, they do it worse.  Whats worse is that for over a year, Verant totally dismissed our complaints and commentary on the spells, they uniformly ignored the points we raised, or if they bothered to comment would simply say &quot;it hits more targets and has a bigger radius&quot; as if that somehow justifies the horrific mana cost and low damage.<br>
<br>
Now, lets add to this Verant's prediliction with calling Al'Kabor the greatest Wizard in all Norrath, and their constant use of him in the game.  He's their new favorite guy, like their spokesman lately, he's showed up in the game in more events and game changes than their cover girl Fironia Vie.  This is the guy they chose to represent Wizards and his spell line is atrocious, its pathetic.  Now, while I'm not going to go so far as to say they are mocking us; what this guy represents to Wizards is not the most powerful of us, but rather the perfect expression of Verant's stunning lack of knowledge and understanding of the class.  He's the poster boy for Verant ignorance.<br>
<br>
So yeah, we hate him.  He's a putz, he gave us awful spells when we NEED better ones, and he mocks us by his presence in the game over and over.  Add to that how he's responsible for translocates that require reagents as people have noted, and a pathetic attempt at pandering by Verant &quot;here guys, an uber item, isn't Al'Kabor cool?  What's that, it looks like a shovel and is better in many ways than the epic?&quot; and we have a guy that really is a focus of anger.<br>
<br>
So no, its not because he's an erudite and its not jealousy.  No Wizard is jealous of this putz, we want him put down like a spastic loudmouth who makes everyone look bad.  He represents all that is wrong with Verant's handling of the class.<br>
